</p>
<p>a national human rights institution, and urged it to enact laws  on the status of refugees 
</p>
<p>and asylum seekers. It raised the issue of children with disabilities.  
</p>
<p>74. Slovenia welcomed the ratification of the Convention on the Rights of Persons 
</p>
<p>with Disabilities, the Istanbul Convention and the Optional Protocol to the Convention 
</p>
<p>on the Rights of the Child on a communications procedure as in its previous 
</p>
<p>recommendation and encouraged the Government to pursue the ratification of the 
</p>
